"{\"uid\": \"si.com-college-cal-other-sports-only-11-countries-won-more-olympic-medals-than-cal-at-paris-01j5183vp5d8\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"In this story:  The Paris Olympic are in the books and only 11 countries claimed more Olympic hardware than the Bears\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099 total of 23 medals.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 140, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 20, \"end\": 25, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999469528135, \"rank\": 5.304726232213302e-08, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Eighteen athletes with Cal affiliations totaled those 23 medals, three of them coming during Sunday's final action.\", \"from\": 142, \"to\": 257, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 165, \"end\": 168, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California_Golden_Bears\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.224605854334168e-22, \"text\": \"Cal\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California_Golden_Bears\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California_Golden_Bears\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Swimmer Ryan Murphy, in his third Olympics, led the way.\", \"from\": 259, \"to\": 315, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 267, \"end\": 278, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/San_Francisco_Giants_minor_league_players\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.0871705466425025e-14, \"text\": \"Ryan Murphy\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/San_Francisco_Giants_minor_league_players\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/San_Francisco_Giants_minor_league_players\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 29-year-old added three medals to his collection, picking up a gold in the mixed 4x200 medley relay, a silver in the men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s 4x100 medley relay and a bronze in the 100 backstroke.\", \"from\": 316, \"to\": 499, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Murphy, unlikely to return to the Games at Los Angeles in 2028, returns home with nine career Olympics medals, five of them gold.\", \"from\": 501, \"to\": 630, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 544, \"end\": 555, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.9999997299210374, \"rank\": 2.699811870606653e-07, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Swimmers Abby Weitzeil, Jack Alexy and Hunter Armstrong, a member of the pre-Olympics training group at Cal, each won two medals.\", \"from\": 632, \"to\": 761, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 641, \"end\": 645, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Abby_Newman\", \"score\": 0.9999995756394119, \"rank\": 4.2435552808929993e-07, \"text\": \"Abby\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Abby_Newman\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Abby_Newman\"}, {\"begin\": 656, \"end\": 660, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jack_Branning\", \"score\": 0.6885883350841275, \"rank\": 0.23331099925615514, \"text\": \"Jack\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jack_Branning\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jack_Branning\"}, {\"begin\": 671, \"end\": 687, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hunter_Armstrong\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Hunter Armstrong\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hunter_Armstrong\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hunter_Armstrong\"}, {\"begin\": 736, \"end\": 739, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California_Golden_Bears\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.224605854334168e-22, \"text\": \"Cal\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California_Golden_Bears\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California_Golden_Bears\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Camryn Rogers won Cal\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s only individual gold medal in Paris, capturing the women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s hammer throw to go with her world championship title of a year ago.\\u00c2  The 25-year-old, who set the collegiate record and won three NCAA titles at Cal, became the first female Golden Bear to win any Olympic medal in track and field.\", \"from\": 763, \"to\": 1081, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 763, \"end\": 776, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Camryn_Rogers\", \"score\": 0.9999999840470083, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Camryn Rogers\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Camryn_Rogers\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Camryn_Rogers\"}, {\"begin\": 819, \"end\": 824, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999469528135, \"rank\": 5.304726232213302e-08, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 981, \"end\": 985, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Collegiate_Athletic_Association\", \"score\": 0.9999987499894442, \"rank\": 1.2500080750590442e-06, \"text\": \"NCAA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Collegiate_Athletic_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Collegiate_Athletic_Association\"}, {\"begin\": 996, \"end\": 999, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California_Golden_Bears\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.224605854334168e-22, \"text\": \"Cal\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California_Golden_Bears\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California_Golden_Bears\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She also helped her native Canada sweep the hammer throw, with Ethan Katzberg capturing the men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s title.\", \"from\": 1082, \"to\": 1188, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1109, \"end\": 1115, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_men's_national_ice_hockey_team\", \"score\": 0.6302458787354356, \"rank\": 0.5805900987170742, \"text\": \"Canada\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_men's_national_ice_hockey_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_men's_national_ice_hockey_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Bears suffered a near-miss in the men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s discus, where Lithuanian Mykolas Alekna lost the gold medal by two inches to Jamaica\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Roje Stona.\", \"from\": 1190, \"to\": 1336, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1250, \"end\": 1260, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lithuania\", \"score\": 0.987306818086764, \"rank\": 0.008960566262581088, \"text\": \"Lithuanian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lithuania\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lithuania\"}, {\"begin\": 1261, \"end\": 1275, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mykolas_Alekna\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Mykolas Alekna\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mykolas_Alekna\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mykolas_Alekna\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Alekna, a junior at Cal, broke the 38-year-old world record in the discus last spring and at Paris broke the Olympic record held by his father, two-time gold medalist Virgijus Alekna, at the 2004 Games.\\u00c2  Mykolas Alekna, who at 21 was trying to become the youngest gold medalist since 1956, won silver with a best throw of 229 feet, 6 inches (69.97 meters).\", \"from\": 1338, \"to\": 1695, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1358, \"end\": 1361, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California_Golden_Bears\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.224605854334168e-22, \"text\": \"Cal\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California_Golden_Bears\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California_Golden_Bears\"}, {\"begin\": 1431, \"end\": 1436, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999469528135, \"rank\": 5.304726232213302e-08, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1543, \"end\": 1557, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mykolas_Alekna\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Mykolas Alekna\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mykolas_Alekna\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mykolas_Alekna\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Stona, a former Clemson and Arkansas athlete, threw 229-8 (70.00 meters).\", \"from\": 1696, \"to\": 1769, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1712, \"end\": 1719, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clemson_Tigers\", \"score\": 0.9976232752603761, \"rank\": 0.0017493721476406778, \"text\": \"Clemson\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clemson_Tigers\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clemson_Tigers\"}, {\"begin\": 1724, \"end\": 1732, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arkansas_Razorbacks\", \"score\": 0.9999994108581548, \"rank\": 4.2750562400690904e-07, \"text\": \"Arkansas\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arkansas_Razorbacks\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arkansas_Razorbacks\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"No doubt the most surprising Cal medalist was 30-year-old Georgia Bell, a 1,500-meter runner from Great Britain, who won bronze with a national-record performance.\", \"from\": 1771, \"to\": 1934, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1800, \"end\": 1803, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California_Golden_Bears\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.224605854334168e-22, \"text\": \"Cal\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California_Golden_Bears\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California_Golden_Bears\"}, {\"begin\": 1829, \"end\": 1836, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Georgia_Bulldogs\", \"score\": 0.9999721050465165, \"rank\": 2.7460407987374002e-05, \"text\": \"Georgia\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Georgia_Bulldogs\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Georgia_Bulldogs\"}, {\"begin\": 1869, \"end\": 1882, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.999999992834546, \"rank\": 4.457375462988419e-09, \"text\": \"Great Britain\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Bell had an unremarkable career at Cal, then stepped away from running for more than four years.\", \"from\": 1936, \"to\": 2032, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1971, \"end\": 1974, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California_Golden_Bears\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.224605854334168e-22, \"text\": \"Cal\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California_Golden_Bears\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California_Golden_Bears\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But against a field of runners that included six of the 13 fastest in history including the world-recordholder, she shaved four seconds off her best time to finish third at 3:52.61, moving her to No.\", \"from\": 2033, \"to\": 2232, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"11 on the all-time world list.\", \"from\": 2233, \"to\": 2263, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And on Sunday, after a 16-year wait, the USA men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s water polo team \\u00